13/07/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Economy Minister and chief negotiator with the EU Ali Babacan urged the international community Tuesday (12 July) to support Turkey' fight against terrorism. 
Speaking to the foreign affairs committee of the European Parliament, Babacan condemned last week's terrorist attacks in London and stressed the need for international collaboration against terrorist violence. 
Turkey has battled the Kurdistan Workers' Party for decades now. 
(NTV - 12/07/05)
